routeFacts.name: ScotRail Express: Edinburgh - Glasgow
routeFacts.description: ScotRail Express: Edinburgh - Glasgow is an upcoming UK Route for Train Sim World 3. It features the iconic Edinburgh - Glasgow via Falkirk High line, with recent upgrade works reflected. The route will include the BR Class 385 EMU in ScotRail's Saltire livery. Players will be able to explore Edinburgh Waverley and Glasgow Queen Street, the second terminal in Glasgow, after Glasgow Central. The route runs for 47 miles (77km) and has 8 intermediate stations.
routeInfo: The Edinburgh - Glasgow line has an abundance of Landmarks. Edinburgh Waverley and Glasgow Queen Street stations themselves surely count, but with the line running through Edinburgh City Centre, it doesn't miss much. The Scott Monument, Edinburgh Castle, National Gallery of Scotland, Princes Street Gardens, Balmoral Hotel, as well as the historic Old and New Towns of Edinburgh overlook as you depart the City.
